data.meta_description: Barry Paul Gibby Gibbs (born September 28, 1948 in Lloydminster, Saskatchewan and raised in Calgary, Alberta) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey defenceman. data.text:
Playing career

During his NHL career, Gibbs played for the Boston Bruins, Minnesota North Stars, Atlanta Flames, St. Louis Blues and Los Angeles Kings. He retired in 1981.
